cs.SY, cs.CE, q-bio.QM, q-bio.TO, q-bio.SC 

Reasoning: The paper deals with modelling and analysis of biological hybrid automata, which involves both control theory and biological systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) which deals with computational methods in various fields including biology. The paper also mentions haemoglobin production in erythrocytes, which falls under the sub-categories q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods) and q-bio.TO (Tissues and Organs). Finally, the paper also involves LPs and semidefinite relaxations, which are commonly used in optimization and computational complexity theory, hence q-bio.SC (Subcellular Processes) is also a possible sub-category.
